{
  "texts": [
    "Traditional programming teaching methods may have difficulty to meet diverse learning needs due to the inherent limitations of a one-size-fits-all approach, reliance on static resources, and limited personalized feedback (Cheah, 2020; Polat & Yilmaz, 2022).",
    "On the other hand, AI-driven tools can adapt to individual student progress, providing customized exercises, tutorials, and feedback that address to each learner's specific strengths and weaknesses (Becker et al., 2023; Silva et al., 2024).",
    "In this regard, chatbots built using large language models (LLMs) like ChatGPT have emerged as powerful tools that can support learners by generating code, offering explanations, and providing personalized feedback (Lo, 2023).",
    "These AI-driven capabilities can help students to understand complex programming concepts, debug their code, and develop problem-solving skills, thereby facilitating a more interactive and supportive learning environment at their own pace (Lo et al., 2024; Philbin, 2023; Wu & Yu, 2024).",
    "Previous research has revealed that AI integration can significantly enhance students' performance in programming education (Zhou, 2023)."
  ]
}